---
import StoryLayout from '../../layouts/StoryLayout.astro';
---

<StoryLayout 
  title="Story Template"
  subtitle="Replace this with your story's subtitle or key insight"
  date="2026-05-28"
  author="Your Name"
>
  <!-- 
    This is a template for editorial stories. Replace the content sections below
    with your actual narrative, insights, and visualizations.
    
    Future narrative components to use:
    - Hero: Opening section with visual
    - KeyInsight: Highlighted key points
    - ChartNarrative: Charts with context
    - PullQuote: Emphasized quotes
    - StatGrid: Structured data
    - StickyFigure: Scroll-driven visuals
    - ExecutiveSummary: Content summaries
  -->

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2>Opening Section</h2>
    <p>
      Start your story here. This introductory section should establish the topic, 
      provide context, and draw the reader in. Think of this as setting the scene 
      for the narrative that follows.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-purple-50 rounded-lg border border-blue-200 p-8 my-8 space-y-4">
    <h2>Key Insight or Finding</h2>
    <p>
      Present your main finding, discovery, or turning point. This is where you 
      surface the most important takeaway that your analysis reveals.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2>Context & Background</h2>
    <p>
      Provide the necessary context for readers to understand the story. What led 
      to this situation? What historical or market factors are relevant?
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2>Data & Evidence</h2>
    <p>
      This section can include charts, statistics, and visualizations from your 
      analysis. Placeholder for charts and data visualizations that support your narrative.
    </p>
    <div class="flex items-center justify-center bg-gray-100 border-2 border-dashed border-gray-300 rounded-lg py-20">
      <div class="text-center text-gray-500">
        <svg class="w-12 h-12 mx-auto mb-4 opacity-50" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
          <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M7 12l3-3 3 3M7 12h10m-10 0l-3 3 3 3m10 0l3 3-3 3m-10 0h10"></path>
        </svg>
        <p class="font-medium">[Chart/Visualization will go here]</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2>Analysis</h2>
    <p>
      Deep dive into what the data means. Analyze patterns, implications, and 
      what this signals for the future. Connect the data to real-world impact.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2>Implications & Next Steps</h2>
    <p>
      What are the consequences of these findings? What should stakeholders 
      consider moving forward? What questions does this raise for future research?
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="space-y-4">
    <h2>Conclusion</h2>
    <p>
      Close the narrative by tying key insights together. What's the takeaway? 
      How does this story fit into the bigger picture?
    </p>
  </section>
</StoryLayout>
